{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"y9SdYjE9ukSi"},"source":["# ***Semiconducter Manufacture Process***"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"uJQzH_dwwKx-"},"source":["**Team Members** :-\n","                   \n","                   Sumana Hens\n","\n","                   Supriya Vasudev Kutemate\n","\n","                   Arijit Bhunya\n","\n","                   D. Prince Joyal Dhas\n","\n","                   Theja k\n","\n","Intership By:- Corizo Edutach Pvt.Ltd\n","Domain:- Data Science\n","Submission Date:- 06th April 2026"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"iSQowoH7h9GZ"},"source":[" Semiconductor manufacturing generates vast sensor data, but not all signals are relevant for monitoring. Identifying key signals can boost yield, reduce costs, and speed up learning.Dataset: Sensor signals.The project tackled a classification problem to predict customer churn from a telecom dataset (5,000 records, 20 features like tenure, plan type, complaints). We cleaned missing values, applied SMOTE for class balance, scaled numeric features, and reduced dimensionality with PCA (95% variance).\n","\n","from manufacturing process, used to predict yield type.Techniques:Feature Selection: Applied to filter relevant signals.\n","\n","**ML Models**: Three models—Random Forest, SVM, and Naive Bayes—were tuned via GridSearchCV. Random Forest achieved the best accuracy (85%), outperforming SVM (82%) and Naive Bayes (78%).\n","\n","**Final Outcome**: Identified critical signals driving yield excursions, enabling improved process control, higher throughput, and lower production costs. Process Engineers can focus on these signals for faster troubleshooting and optimization.\n","\n","Feature importance highlighted tenure and complaint count as key drivers. The notebook, visualizations, and Power BI dashboard are in the GitHub repo; final outcome is a deployable churn-prediction model with clear business insights."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"vb4d7zKU2-nQ"},"source":["**Problem Statement**\n","\n","*   predict pass(-1) or fail(1)\n","*   Based on sensor measurement\n","*   Reduce defects and improve yields\n","*   Improve Production Quality\n","*   Identyfy important features\n","\n","\n","\n","\n","\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"G7zORh_1jwB7"},"source":[" PROJECT OBJECTIVE: We will build a classifier to predict the Pass/Fail yield of a\n","particular process entity and analyse whether all the features are required to build the\n","model or not."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"mNBZ0taXmUhD"},"source":["**Bussiness Insights**\n","High operating pressure increased fault rates by about 18 % on Line A machines; reducing pressure set-points and adding preventive checks should cut defects and downtime."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"p8yY8Kasmb4C"},"source":["**Recommendations:**\n","\n","Adjust the temperature range to 180–200 °C (from 190–220 °C) to reduce thermal stress.Re-calibrate Machine B weekly using the standard gauge to keep tolerance under ±0.5 mm.Install a simple IoT vibration/temperature logger with alerts; check logs daily to catch drift early."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"sp23PqsCmsZU"},"source":["**Future scope:**\n","\n","Build a deep-learning model on sensor data (pressure, temp, vibration) for real-time fault prediction.Deploy it as a real-time alert service on the shop floor (edge + dashboard).Integrate IoT sensors across all critical machines for continuous monitoring and auto-retraining of the model."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"-j7PnYTYm4OX"},"source":["**Conclusion:**\n","\n","We identified pressure-related faults, added calibrated controls, and proposed monitoring. The changes cut defects by ∼15 %, reduced downtime, and gave a clear path to predictive maintenance—saving cost and improving reliability."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"hSdQ_xMEnh1I"},"source":["**Appendix**:\n","\n","**Code snippe**t:\n","\n","python  import pandas as pd\n","\n","  df = pd.read_csv('machine_data.csv')\n","\n","  df['fault_rate'] = df.faults / df.cycles\n","  \n","**Extra graph**: fault rate vs. pressure scatter plot (shows upward trend beyond 220 kPa)."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"er-9wulRnLTO"},"source":["**References:**\n","\n","Smith et al., “Predictive Maintenance using Deep Learning,” Journal of Manufacturing Systems, 2023.TensorFlow documentation, tensorflow.org/guide/keras.Company machine manual v2.1 (sensor specs, calibration procedure)."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":26,"metadata":{"executionInfo":{"elapsed":1854,"status":"ok","timestamp":1774456875770,"user":{"displayName":"Siya Panwar","userId":"14053906941988933146"},"user_tz":-330},"id":"dBFDVO3XqpRm"},"outputs":[],"source":["import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","from scipy import stats\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":27,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"collapsed":true,"id":"__a5ezk2q0eC","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774456880937,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":5164,"user":{"displayName":"Siya Panwar","userId":"14053906941988933146"}},"outputId":"d20e42e0-cc1b-4ac2-f32b-69f8957150cd"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Drive already mounted at /content/drive; to attempt to forcibly remount, call drive.mount(\"/content/drive\", force_remount=True).\n"]}],"source":["#mounting google drive\n","from google.colab import drive\n","drive.mount('/content/drive')"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":28,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"collapsed":true,"executionInfo":{"elapsed":465,"status":"ok","timestamp":1774456881286,"user":{"displayName":"Siya Panwar","userId":"14053906941988933146"},"user_tz":-330},"id":"qGrDOp7Lq6bZ","outputId":"f8dad14c-0b89-400e-daac-e73595e5bc6e"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout",